29913.title: Cutlery37.wav
29913.description: Series of samples of cutlery in a Tupperware box. I rummaged about with my hand in this box in order to make noises that will be used in the rhythm section of a number of songs I’m working on. They are recorded with a Leem SR-105 dynamic microphone through an Edirol UA-25 directly on my computer. Such samples are very usable to create non-standard rhythm patterns, e.g. by looping them or by by putting them randomly in a song. These samples are the non-processed ones (even no noise reduction) in order to give you maximum freedom to manipulate the original recordings.
